  "body": "\r\n***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: Keyboard overlaps message input in public modal chat screen on iPhone. If the predictive text is enabled on the device then it also overlaps message input.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nKeyboard does not overlap message input in public modal chat screen on iPhone\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nKeyboard overlaps message input in public modal chat screen on iPhone\r\n<img width=\"300\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-09-25 at 14 23 26\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/46011487-a5aa5680-c0ce-11e8-8544-871a94f7b3e3.png\">\r\n<img width=\"304\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-09-25 at 14 23 47\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/46011489-a8a54700-c0ce-11e8-89db-340c43b1f564.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status and create an account on iPhone\r\n- Navigate to any Dapp (e.g. Simple Test Dapp)   \r\n- At the webview bottom tap PublicChatModal icon\r\n- Put the cursor in message input\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Develop 0.9.29 (9068); node 0.15.0\r\n* Operating System: iOS only",
